msContents.summary: The Provincial Law of Jutland. AM 4 4to is the oldest extant manuscript containing The Provincial Law of Jutland in Denmark.

msItem.title: The Provincial Law of Jutland
Jyske lov

filiation.p: A copy, AM 11 4to, has been made of this manuscript.

foliation.p: The manuscript is foliated in the top right-hand corners.

layout.p: The manuscript is written in long lines with 23 lines to the page. Rubrics are in red and pen-flourished majuscules in red or blue. There are column headings.

handNote.p: The manuscript is written in a Gothic Bookhand.
In the chapter on sorcery, the shade of the ink is lighter than the rest of the text and could therefore be a later addition.

additions.p: Some marginal references are found. In the left margin of fol. 70v a profile of a man is found, and on fols 4v and 5v there are animals.

binding.p: Bound in a parchment binding (an old sea chart) from the beginning of the eighteenth century (1700-1730) ; 222 160 33 . On the front fly-leaf Kristian Kålund has noted the date 14.08.1886.

origin.p: The manuscript was written in Denmark. It has been dated c. 1400 by Kristian Kålund ( Katalog I 341 ). Later, Peter Skautrup dated the manuscript to c. 1350, except from The Chapter on Sorcery which he hesitatingly dates to the beginning of the fifteenth century ( Skautrup 1933 xvi ). However, all of the manuscript is now thought to date from as early as c. 1300 ( Kroman 1943 57 ).

custEvent.p: Lent to The Danish National Archives (Rigsarkivet), Copenhagen, for the use of Erik Kroman 1957-58, 1959 (twice), 1961 (twice), 1965 and 1967.
Lent to The State and University Library (Statsbiblioteket), Århus, for the use of Peter Skautrup 1969-70.

Lent to The Provincial Archives of Northern Jutland (Landsarkivet for Nørrejylland), Viborg, November 1990 to August 1991, and later to The Royal Library (Det Kongelige Bibliotek), Copenhagen, August to December 1991 for the exhibition, 730-året for jydske lov (The 730th Anniversary of the Provincial Law of Jutland).
